<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Verant needs to make the system work</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:43 p.m. 25/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Verant needs to make the system work<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1711" TARGET=_self>Racial Annimosity</A> (Hawthorne)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>This has long been a concern of mine that two groups would emerge, with guilds being on one side of the fence and ignoring racial boundaries. The only solution to this predicament is for Verant to get tough on the faction hits that players take when killing other players of the same race (or even good on good, etc). If this is enforced, and players lose town access due to faction hits, then the majority of players, guilds included, will adopt this style of play. Without it, powergamers will always be powergamers and will choose the race/class combo's they feel best further their goals.
<P>I will continue to refrain from looting members of my own race, and won't attack same race players. I cannot expect or depend on others to do the same.
<P>&gt; Hiya Rain, lemme take a stab at this.
<BR>&gt; Most people have a character prefrence such as halfing, elf etc.
<BR>&gt; I understand your point about class warfare, and good race's and
<BR>&gt; bad race's and how they dont mix in the RPG Environment that 989
<BR>&gt; has in place. However, a large majority of the Core PvP
<BR>&gt; community overlook that and have choosen thier race based off of
<BR>&gt; class statistics and , and not how that race may stand socially
<BR>&gt; in the RPG aspect of the game. Its purley a powergamer move. The
<BR>&gt; PvP server IMHO will house 2 distinct factions, the pure racial
<BR>&gt; factions, and then the Guild factions. Ofcourse guild factions
<BR>&gt; will ignore the racial balance of the game for the most part
<BR>&gt; inorder to serve the guild and play as a unit (again, a
<BR>&gt; powergamer move).
<P>&gt; I would suggest that people on this server get familliar with
<BR>&gt; the guilds that are represneted there. This may make it easy on
<BR>&gt; some players to understand why there isnt going to be
<BR>&gt; "racial harmony" amoung your own race.
<P>&gt; Agreed totaly. The thing about the PvP server is that it is just
<BR>&gt; that, PvP, home of the K-RaD dudes, kewlz00r pk's, good evil
<BR>&gt; role players, hard-core antis, the solo killer, the asshole,
<BR>&gt; powergammers, Lynch mobs, and the typical RPG player.
<P>&gt; My advice to people is that if you arent willing to deal with
<BR>&gt; the diversities of the PvP server such as inner racial
<BR>&gt; annimosity or looting and dueling constantly, then I suggest
<BR>&gt; another server.
<P>&gt; Hawthorne EQ-Adept, Council - The Regulators
<BR>&gt; www.theregulators.org
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
